    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.13-15_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Border of Roses and Music Notes Along the Left Margin</figDesc>
                </figure>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        State Hospital No. I.
                        Fulton, Missouri
                        October 16- 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John Niedhart<sic>Neihardt</sic></addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Poet: <hi rend="caps">T.V.</hi> Series</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">U.</hi> of Columbia</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>My dear Dr. Niedhart<sic>Neihardt</sic>&#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Altho<sic>although</sic> I am <del/><add>a</add> patient I get much goodness and pleasure from your beautiful, flowing reading&#8212; and it is great that you are as well the Author.!</p>
                
                <p>It must mean a lot to your actual students.</p>
                
                <p>I would like to "squeeze" in and say these things, I believe I like the Indians. I long for Indian Craft-bead-work to do but never get it. I believe I am the "Comanche" type &#8212; Is Chief Crazy Horse of the new, remarkable sculptor near Mt. Rushmore
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.13-15_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>  
                <fw type="authorial">- 2 -</fw>
                
                    Lwanah Parker of the Comanches&#8212;the feather alone is 44 feet high-it says.</p>
                
                <p>My nieces' mother is of Nebraska and is Valdictorian of her class <add>there.</add> We have a Night Supervisor from there. Mrs. MaryAnn Snider <hi rend="caps">R.N.</hi> &#8212; [I have taken a Practical Nursing course &#8212; Correspondence; but never used it; I hope so, someday, to do. I have 3 children: girl + 2 boys baby 6. Mrs. Snider once set her cap on my head!!!]-</p>
                
                <p>These four years have been something; was more active the years I was at the Clinic under Electric Shock Treatments under Dr. <hi rend="caps"><del/><add>E.</add>S.</hi> Waraich.</p>
                
                <p>I am quite a ball fan &#8212; I think &#8212; and was so partial to the Braves of Milwaukee that I really felt it when they lost. Great Games they played.</p>
                
                <p>I am interested in your series, in speech of which your reading quite impresses me, and I would hope for an autograph from you, if possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully</salute>
                    
                    <signed>(Mrs) Lucille Wolf.</signed>
                    
                    <address><addrLine>Mrs. Lucille <hi rend="caps">M.</hi> Wolf.- 8-South.</addrLine></address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
